<subSubSection id="34BCD16FEB13009307747442A0158677" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="701C83E6648880BCA2C0EA7AC9D4C174" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D2519BE2EA88FC2C06985E216B0DB84A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Suffruticose plant, forming distant, rather solitary, erect stems. 
<emphasis id="5E336365FDEC865FC7D3ED3A0BA448F3" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rhizomes</emphasis>
6-10 
<normalizedToken id="9AAFEC44D2A67DDC150344ACBF285961" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.3 cm, horizontal to oblique, glabrous. 
<emphasis id="B95577A5559F5916F88613BEA10B984C" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Stems</emphasis>
12-20 cm tall, usually simple, sometimes branched at the upper part, covered with adpressed, arachnoid trichomes, with leaves restricted to the upper part. 
<emphasis id="37B722FB37997282C85F0222073758EA" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Leaves</emphasis>
imbricate, extending into a sheath-like base that bears arachnoid trichomes; leaf laminas 4.6-5 
<normalizedToken id="DBA332CD68C63D6537D23769136FA814" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
ca. 0.9 mm, linear-acicular, aristate at the apex (arista up to 1 mm long, purplish), entire, terete in cross section, glabrous, unconspicuously nerved on both faces, somewhat fleshy, drying coriaceous, matte, papillose. 
<emphasis id="C4F23E936619B203922C9023CE7B7BF4" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Capitula</emphasis>
radiate, erect, sessile, partially enclosed among the leaves. 
<emphasis id="038D1944E6AA0DB6033E21B71E2E6F11" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Involucres</emphasis>
ca. 8.6 
<normalizedToken id="FF884BC7C483A216EBE3037E2C3A5893" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.3 mm, cupuliform; involucral bracts ca. 13, 5.2-5.5 
<normalizedToken id="9FF5D94336242E30D43A93D82A085DA9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.1-1.6 mm, rather acute at the apex, dark-purplish. 
<emphasis id="78BC0D51CD03B57A312A91DB30AB5084" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ray florets</emphasis>
ca. 13; corollas ca. 12 
<normalizedToken id="0C4254B26F38F59736EEC663D6849944" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.3-2.5 mm, 4 to 5-veined, subentire to 3-toothed at the apex, conspicuously surpassing the involucre, white, purplish beneath. 
<emphasis id="7B785226C4CE551EE314A48D187F9F9B" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Disc florets</emphasis>
ca. 50; corollas 3.8-4.2 mm long, pale yellow to creamy; style branches truncate with a crown of sweeping trichomes, yellowish. 
<emphasis id="3FC5EF06DB57628AF77034FD5FB22674" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Achenes</emphasis>
cylindrical, with scattered arachnoid trichomes (immature); pappus 3.1-3.3 mm long, barbellate, whitish. Chromosome number unknown. Fig. 
<figureCitation id="974FF3A94A14A5140F5694FA52361A0F" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Xenophyllum acerosum A habit B stem apical part and capitulum C detail of leaf surface D adaxial leaf surface E ray corolla and style F disc corolla and stamens (vertically sectioned, style removed) G disc corolla and style branches H style I immature achene with pappus. All details drawn from Prieto 280 (US). Illustration by Alice Tangerini." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.158.50848.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448885" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="403D5BD1431F62D5E853D286047EADBD" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.158.50848.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448885" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
