<subSubSection id="6B11B055D1EB8DF97348C6C1BB69575F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FCE37FCEAA0B714C170FBE0FEF4E0857" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B99302940493AF87370C6EE0BA0D9FDE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Endemic to Ecuador (Azuay, Zamora-Chinchipe [expected]). It grows in marshy places of the paramo ecoregion, between elevations of 3050-3070 m (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6A011E7BA4689274359A28E8B66C0FA9" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Distribution map of Xenophyllum acerosum (left hand) and X. humile (right hand)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.158.50848.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448886" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1E26A542DCAC68D3CFC6DF0AA16420B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Thus far, 
<taxonomicName id="80525DEFA9F4BD3AEC1D851D58D37D03" genus="X." lsidName="X. acerosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="acerosum">
<emphasis id="CE83FBC3652D2B4A752DCBDC7282DB32" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">X. acerosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the type locality in the paramo of Yacumbi, which is located above Saraguro on the border between the Ecuadorian provinces of Azuay and Zamora-Chinchipe.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8CF8AA17103A57F75FFDCA2FB71AB9FF" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.158.50848.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448886" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
